    {
      "id": "pPxlznDXAbeD3cYj7OBuT",
      "questionNumber": 4,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "section": "A",
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "questionText": "The “N” which does <b>not</b> contribute to the basicity for the compound is :\n<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l82y7rvn/5c734e65-ecee-45e2-9273-a4429fb5f1bb/b8e10330-34e6-11ed-b84c-a3c7c2456516/file-1l82y7rvo.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l82y7rvn/5c734e65-ecee-45e2-9273-a4429fb5f1bb/b8e10330-34e6-11ed-b84c-a3c7c2456516/file-1l82y7rvo.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2016 (Online) 10th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 226 English\">",
      "options": [
        "N 7",
        "N 9",
        "N 1",
        "N 3"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "solution": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l82y8j1l/9d9a17b6-8f68-4236-871b-6be95fadad0c/cddd0590-34e6-11ed-b84c-a3c7c2456516/file-1l82y8j1m.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l82y8j1l/9d9a17b6-8f68-4236-871b-6be95fadad0c/cddd0590-34e6-11ed-b84c-a3c7c2456516/file-1l82y8j1m.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2016 (Online) 10th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 226 English Explanation\">\n<br>In this aromatic compound, the lone of N9 is participate in resonance with the compound and complete the aromatic system. So this lone pair is delocalised and can not gain proton (H<sup>+</sup>)\n<br><br>When an atom is already part of $$\\pi $$ bond then the lone pair of the atom can not participate in resonance. That  lone pair is  called localised lone pair.\n<br><br>Here in N1, N3 and N7 all the lone pairs are localised. As those lone pair do not participate in resonance so it can gain proton (H<sup>+</sup>) so those lone pair will increase the basicity of the compound.",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Compounds Containing Nitrogen"
    },
