      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "section": "A",
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "questionText": "<p>Isomeric amines with molecular formula C$$_8$$H$$_{11}$$N give the following tests</p>\n<p>Isomer (P) $$\\Rightarrow$$ Can be prepared by Gabriel phthalimide synthesis</p>\n<p>Isomer (Q) $$\\Rightarrow$$ Reacts with Hinsberg's reagent to give solid insoluble in NaOH</p>\n<p>Isomer (R) $$\\Rightarrow$$ Reacts with HONO followed by $$\\beta$$-naphthol in NaOH to give red dye.</p>\n<p>Isomers (P), (Q) and (R) respectively are</p>",
      "options": [
        "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lgzng1h5/aff4852c-228a-440c-b06b-bf46eddfd45b/32ce9690-e544-11ed-8d50-d941312069b0/file-1lgzng1h6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lgzng1h5/aff4852c-228a-440c-b06b-bf46eddfd45b/32ce9690-e544-11ed-8d50-d941312069b0/file-1lgzng1h6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 10th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 82 English Option 1\">",
        "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lgznfqx7/ac3f4e44-9522-40fa-a98b-f352a4e5d4a2/2aa77db0-e544-11ed-8d50-d941312069b0/file-1lgznfqx8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lgznfqx7/ac3f4e44-9522-40fa-a98b-f352a4e5d4a2/2aa77db0-e544-11ed-8d50-d941312069b0/file-1lgznfqx8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 10th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 82 English Option 2\">",
        "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lgznf01i/4df73fa0-a77e-4837-adab-4b3db2f0226c/15e3c960-e544-11ed-8d50-d941312069b0/file-1lgznf01j.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lgznf01i/4df73fa0-a77e-4837-adab-4b3db2f0226c/15e3c960-e544-11ed-8d50-d941312069b0/file-1lgznf01j.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 10th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 82 English Option 3\">",
        "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lgznephd/c23b3eb4-14e7-44ec-9ca6-d4cfb7ffc9b2/0dbb9f10-e544-11ed-8d50-d941312069b0/file-1lgznephe.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lgznephd/c23b3eb4-14e7-44ec-9ca6-d4cfb7ffc9b2/0dbb9f10-e544-11ed-8d50-d941312069b0/file-1lgznephe.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 10th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 82 English Option 4\">"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "solution": "(P) Gabriel phthalimide synthesis is used for the preparation of aliphatic primary amines. Aromatic primary amines cannot be prepared by this method.<br/><br/>\n(Q) $2^{\\circ}$-amines reacts with Hinsberg's reagent to give solid insoluble in $\\mathrm{NaOH}$<br/><br/>\n(R) Aromatic primary amine react with nitrous acid at low temperature $(273-298 \\mathrm{~K})$ to form diazonium salts, which form Red dye with $\\beta$ Naphthol",
