      "id": "1l6e2hux2",
      "questionNumber": 10,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "section": "A",
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "questionText": "<p>The number of sp<sup>3</sup> hybridised carbons in an acyclic neutral compound with molecular formula C<sub>4</sub>H<sub>5</sub>N is ___________.</p>",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "solution": "$\\mathrm{C}_{4} \\mathrm{H}_{5} \\mathrm{~N}$\n<br><br>\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\mathrm{DBE} &amp; =(\\mathrm{C}+1)-\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{H}+\\mathrm{X}-\\mathrm{N}}{2}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&amp; =4+1-\\left(\\frac{5-1}{2}\\right)=5-2=3\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n<br><br>\n3 double bond equivalent are present in compound<br><br>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lc5o1v78/db6bab18-b0e3-447a-abe0-4b9054852745/30c32f40-8596-11ed-a4e1-239777dab634/file-1lc5o1v79.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lc5o1v78/db6bab18-b0e3-447a-abe0-4b9054852745/30c32f40-8596-11ed-a4e1-239777dab634/file-1lc5o1v79.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 25th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 121 English Explanation\"><br>\nOnly 1 $s p^{3}$ hybridised carbon is there\n<br><br>\n(Keeping compound as acyclic)",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Compounds Containing Nitrogen"
    },
    {
      "id": "B9RemIihTHRDJ7fS",
      "questionNumber": 11,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "section": "A",
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "questionText": "The increasing order of basicity of the following compounds is :\n<img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/xatzUhhzOuX1GW2qd/M80i6CbpnJqncSeXdEB3oxdwP1Sh5/xfGhpSZiad2aVQhFCrLg0k/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2018 (Offline) Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 238 English\">",
      "options": [
        "(d) &lt; (b) &lt; (a) &lt; (c)",
        "(a) &lt; (b) &lt; (c) &lt; (d)",
        "(b) &lt; (a) &lt; (c) &lt; (d)",
        "(b) &lt; (a) &lt; (d) &lt; (c)"
      ],
      "correctOption": 3,
      "solution": "Among all the given compounds the  basic nature depends upon their tendency to donate the electron pair. \n<br><br><img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/whnuJZ43uIiRm1RZ6/OwZ4qSoslXAnRJt5KOezBgPaOYmyQ/bgo3niW20YqqHN8qzZbqJ8/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2018 (Offline) Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 238 English Explanation 1\"> \n<br><br>Because of +M effect of $$-$$NH<sub>2</sub>, lone pair will make $$\\pi $$ bond and $$\\pi $$ bond will go to $$-$$NH and electron density will increase at $$-$$NH.\n<br><br>Because of +M effect Basic nature of this will make compare to others as in other compounds there is no  +M effect and +M effect has more power than other effect. \n<br><br>Here, in, \n<br><br><img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/s76HZDdQHbEKNPW6C/z1uw2GMyytqLpTsydq1B5rz8EHqTB/9G58MfOB32zgWYpBD4ympd/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2018 (Offline) Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 238 English Explanation 2\">\n<br><br>$$-$$CH<sub>3</sub> has +I effect so in N $$-$$ C bond electron will move towards nitrogen, So electron density increase at nitrogen.\n<br><br>And alkayl group also has +I effect, so it will also increase electron density at nitrogen.\n<br><br>As electron density at nitrogen increases, so tendency to donate electron pair increases and basic nature also increases.\n<br><br>In those following,\n<br><br><img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/X9Hxskvh6QBC1am2W/vtoqmIiYzVT3f6HNHArLZWb83V8Uk/dd7yrsYrMvT2IWdaDONyQv/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2018 (Offline) Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 238 English Explanation 3\">\n<br><br>double bond has ($$-$$ I) effect, it will decrease the availability of lone pair electron at nitrogen but at (b) double bond is closer to nitrogen, so ($$-$$ I) effect will be more powerful than compound at (a), so (b) will be less basic nature.\n<br><br>So, the order of basicity,  c &gt; d &gt; a &gt; b",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Compounds Containing Nitrogen"
    },
